{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-2651"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of measuring, testing, navigating and control equipment"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "2651"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :measuring-control-instrument/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :process-safety :measurement-integrity]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :measuring-control-equipment-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :eda :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies []
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "MeasCtrlAdvisor ⊣ Measuring Control Equipment Plant Operations
 Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for measuring/testing/navigating/
 control-equipment manufacturing (precision-calibration/assembly/
 test lines producing process-control instruments, laboratory
 analytical instruments, test-and-inspection equipment, navigational
 instruments, meters, radiation-detection instruments, surveying
 instruments and meteorological instruments) -- not direct
 calibration/assembly-line-equipment control authority and not a
 metrology-certification authority (e.g. a NIST-traceable calibration
 certificate). Four ops (`:log-production-batch` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect :propose` only. Thirteen
 concrete governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD
 invariants: propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed
 proposal-effect allowlist (no direct calibration/assembly-line-
 equipment control), permanent equipment-actuate block, permanent
 metrology-certification-authority block (this actor never
 self-issues a NIST-traceable calibration certificate), independent
 equipment verification/registration before maintenance scheduling,
 independent batch verification/registration before shipment
 coordination, independent shipment-quantity recompute against the
 batch's own logged production quantity, double-schedule guard,
 instrument-class validation, calibration-accuracy plausibility
 validation, and defect-rate plausibility validation. Safety-concern
 flagging (calibration-drift/precision-defect/electrical-safety
 hazard) ALWAYS escalates to a human plant supervisor;
 `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and
 only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
